Well played to Dove for escaping a horrendous start, and to Name for pulling of the nuts strategy of just announcing your shifts and acting confused.
Both Kirsch and I predicted this was quite village favoured.
So it's impressive to see them make the run they did.
Henners also played a key part in the success of the SC's
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zEsDcEteaNc&feature=youtu.be&ab_channel=Dux0r
That's a "short" runthrough of how the setup came to be, with a look at the script and some last min tweaks.

The random quacking and woofing at the start was purely that, just random stuff to set the tone of the game and spark some discussion around those things, to allow people to hide in them with their mandatory objectives if they desired.
The SC's had to basically announce who they were targeting (quacks if a duck, woofs if a dog etc.)
Only 3 people had the objective to vote for a specific avatar, (one for each set) and one of them was neutral.
So I figured 2 village roles with that limitation wasn't going to be gamebreaking, and would put an interesting constraint on some to actually argue their case but potentially vote elsewhere.
The only person who wasn't allowed to announce their objective was Gio, our insomniac. Who had the simple task of just making up stuff each day.

"Compulsive liar: - Each day you are alive, you need to invent a new negative mechanic that will be applied to players each day and inform the village of what will happen. You cannot tell players this is a lie. (Example: Anyone quacking more than 3 times has a 30% chance to die tonight.) Get creative."

This was essentially to just stir shit and throw some extra spice into the game, and mostly to see how long they could get away with it before people called them on it and lynched them. They did an awesome job.
I really enjoyed watching them come up with stuff.

The evils had a horrendous start. Name opted not to kill n1, Dove targeted Name and Henners was obviously blocked. In subsequent nights there were many instances of them targeted each other or the same target.

Village, unfortunately had a rough time and managed to snatch defeat from the jaws of victory on a few occasions. I honestly have no idea how Name managed to wiggle themselves out of being lynched so often.
I hope you guys had fun with it at least.
